The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, April 3: As part of its workforce restructuring at the Kurla manufacturing unit, Fiat India today said it has accepted the voluntary retirement of more than 50 per cent of its employees at the plant. ?We have accepted VRS scheme of 711 employees out of a total of 1,270 employees,? a Fiat spokesperson said. The company, however, has no plans to shutdown the Kurla unit and this is just a move to rightsize the unit and increase efficiencies, he added.

 New Delhi, April 3: The coal ministry has decided to circulate a fresh cabinet note among the ministries concerned for seeking the cabinets nod to confer on Coal Videsh Limited the status of a CIL subsidiary, contrary to its earlier stand of rendering it an independent entity.

 Mumbai, April 3: Gujarat Gas Company today said it has extended its previous agreement with GAIL which entitles it to source natural gas from the companys distribution plants in Gujarat. 

 Mumbai, April 3: JSW Steel today said it has divested its stake in JSW Energy to Samarth Holdings, a part of the OP Jindal group for Rs 513.69 crore. 

 Mumbai, April 3: Engineering construction company Punj Lloyd has decided to raise Rs 1,000 crore from the international or the domestic market through the issue of FCCBs or other instruments.




